broa de farinha de milho:

Ingredients:
    2 cups of cornmeal
    1 cup of all-purpose flour
    1/2 cup of sugar
    2 eggs
    1/2 cup of milk
    1/2 cup of oil
    1 tablespoon of baking powder
    1 pinch of salt

Instructions:

1) Preheat your oven to 180°C (350°F).
2) In a large bowl, mix together the cornmeal, all-purpose flour, sugar, and salt.
3) In another bowl, beat the eggs until they become frothy.
4) Add the milk and oil to the beaten eggs and mix well.
5) Add the liquid mixture to the bowl with the dry ingredients and mix everything until the batter is smooth.
6) Add the baking powder to the batter and mix a little more.
7) Pour the batter into a greased baking pan and bake for about 30-35 minutes, or until the broa is golden brown and a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
8) Allow the broa to cool down a bit before serving.

This broa de farinha de milho recipe is easy and delicious. You can serve the broa with butter, cheese, or even with a hot cup of coffee. Enjoy!
